.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-PEER-COUNT" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-peer-count \- count total, connected, and disconnected peers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-peer-count
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns peer counts from
.BR listpeers .
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"total":N,"connected":N,"disconnected":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-peer-list (1),
.BR lightning-node-health (1)
